.TH "sysfs_emit_at" 9 "sysfs_emit_at" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sysfs_emit_at \- scnprintf equivalent, aware of PAGE_SIZE buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sysfs_emit_at
.BI "(char *buf "  ","
.BI "int at "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "... "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
start of PAGE_SIZE buffer.
.IP "at" 12
offset in \fIbuf\fP to start write in bytes
\fIat\fP must be >= 0 && < PAGE_SIZE
.IP "fmt" 12
format
.IP "..." 12
optional arguments to \fIfmt\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns number of characters written starting at &\fIbuf\fP[\fIat\fP].
